sftp-jailer (1.2.0~rc1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * v1.2.0 release candidate 1: first .deb release. v1.2 milestone Phase 5
    (Packaging, Install/Purge, Automated Release) is complete and empirically
    verified on Ubuntu 24.04 LTS and Debian 13 (Trixie). Phase 6 (v1.1
    carry-over closure) and Phase 7 (retroactive Nyquist validation authoring)
    are not yet shipped.
  * DIST-02/03: goreleaser + nfpm build CGO-free .deb for amd64 and arm64;
    lintian --pedantic clean.
  * DIST-04: postinst creates the sftp-jailer group, enables and starts the
    weekly observer timer, and pre-initializes /var/lib/sftp-jailer/observations.db
    at the current schema version (hidden init-db subcommand, plan 05-07).
  * DIST-05/09: apt purge removes the binary, both systemd units, state dir,
    /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-sftp-jailer.conf drop-in, and the sftp-jailer
    group; admin-edited /etc/ssh/sshd_config and unrelated drop-ins remain
    byte-identical. SSH session preserved across the cycle.
  * DIST-08: tag-push GitHub Actions workflow runs go test, golangci-lint,
    govulncheck, architectural invariants, goreleaser, lintian --pedantic,
    and uploads .deb + .tar.gz + SHA256SUMS.txt to GitHub Releases.
  * DIST-10: empirical thesis-flow UAT passed on Ubuntu 24.04 (192.168.1.187)
    and Debian 13 (192.168.1.170) lab hosts.
  * v1.1 feature surface (chrooted SFTP, user/key/password CRUD, observation
    pipeline, OPEN/STAGING/LOCKED progressive lockdown with 3-min auto-revert)
    is unchanged and shipped end-to-end.

 -- sftp-jailer-dev <noreply@sftp-jailer.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

sftp-jailer (1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Phase 5 release: packaging, install/purge, automated release pipeline.
  * BUG-05-A fix: add /var/backups/sftp-jailer/ to atomic write allowlist so
    purge-sshd-cleanup drop-in backup succeeds and drop-in is removed on purge.
